        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add LiteLLM provider",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add a LiteLLM API provider that reads `/key/info` and `/user/info` for personal and team budget usage\n- wire LiteLLM into provider registration, token accounts, config/env overrides, icons, widgets, and docs\n- support both LiteLLM auth layouts: the target virtual key remains the `/key/info?key=...` lookup key, while optional `secretKey` / `LITELLM_MANAGEMENT_KEY` can authorize management endpoints when a proxy requires admin/master credentials\n- harden LiteLLM parsing for `/v1` base URLs, quoted environment values, trimmed keys, missing management-key fallback, and arbitrary metadata payloads\n\n## Provider PR comparison\n- Compared against recent provider PRs including Devin (#1264), T3 Chat (#1091), Bedrock (#897), DeepSeek (#811), Chutes (#1496), and Zed (#1517).\n- Scope matches the API-key provider pattern: provider enum/descriptor/implementation, settings store, config/env mapping, docs, icon resources, widget labels, cost scanner support, and focused tests.\n- The extra LiteLLM-specific surface is the optional management key, added to address deployments where `/key/info` and `/user/info` require a more privileged bearer token than the target virtual key.\n\n## Live behavior evidence\n- User-provided curl output from a real LiteLLM proxy showed `/key/info?key=...` returning JSON with `info.user_id`, `info.team_id`, `info.spend`, and key metadata using the same configured bearer key.\n- User-provided curl output from the same proxy showed `/user/info?user_id=...` returning JSON with `user_info.user_id`, `user_info.spend`, `user_info.max_budget`, `keys`, and top-level `teams` data.\n- User-provided curl output also showed `/team/info?team_id=...` returning `team_info.spend`, `team_info.max_budget`, `budget_reset_at`, and key metadata, which matches the budget field names used by the provider parser.\n- The proof is summarized here with all keys, URLs, identifiers, emails, timestamps, and amounts omitted; no live request was re-run from this workspace because no LiteLLM env/config entry is present locally.\n\n## Tests\n- `swift test --filter 'LiteLLMUsageFetcherTests|ProviderConfigEnvironmentTests|ConfigValidationTests' --skip-update`\n- `make check`\n- `make test` (39/39 shards)\n- `./Scripts/compile_and_run.sh` (ad-hoc signed app bundle created and launched)\n- `git diff --check`\n- staged diff scans for long `sk-...` token patterns and UUID-shaped identifiers\n\n## Risk\n- real proxy evidence came from user-provided curl output rather than a repeatable CI/live test; endpoint behavior is covered locally by mocked transport tests\n- HTTP behavior is covered by mocked transport tests, including separate management Bearer auth, target-key query lookup, same-key fallback, and 401 handling before `/user/info`\n- local app launch used ad-hoc signing",
